\section{Discussion}

%% Neutrality of the sequences?
% Are all protein sequences identical?

\subsection{Diversity}

Sea cucumber diversity is underestimated. Regardless of the method used to
estimate ESUs from the genetic data, we recovered more species than we
identified based on accepted taxonomic names. The manual assessment of the ESUs
for the Holothuriidae indicates that the diversity is underestimated by
approximately 50\%. This family is however the most easily accessible as it
inhabits shallow waters, and most species have widespread geographical
distributions. Other families have probably at least comparable if not higher
levels of unrecognized diversity.

The manual delineation of the ESUs indicates that 10\% of the species do not
form reciprocally monophyletic clades separated by a barcoding gap that allow
their delineation based on genetic data alone. These taxa represent either very
recently diverged species forming monophyletic groups but with intra-genetic
distances higher than the distances to their most closely related species (10
out of 15 ESUs), or ESUs that are not monophyletic. Interestingly the 5 ESUs
concerned all belong to the subgenus \textit{Halodeima}: 3 ESUs of
\textit{Holothuria edulis}, \textit{H. mexicana} and
\textit{H. floridana}. Additionally, 2 species of \textit{Actinopyga}, each
represented by a single individual cluster with another \textit{Actinopyga}
species (\textit{A. flammea} and \textit{A. caerulea} are indistinguishable from
\textit{A. palauensis}). The species involved are all unambiguously
morphologically different and could be assigned to the correct species if a
voucher specimen is available. Additionally, we only detected a single case of
putative introgressive hybridization between two species of \textit{Bohadschia}
(see \cite{Kim2013} for more details), in which the putative F1 hybrid has the
intermediate phenotype of its parent species but the COI sequence of either of
its parent species.

Funk and Ormland \cite{Funk2003} estimated that 23\% of the 2,319 animal species
they surveyed were non-monophyletic in their mitochondrial genealogies. In the
Holothuriidae, we recovered a much lower rate of (2.5\%, 5 out of
\Sexpr{length(noGeoGrps)}~ESUs). Funk and Ormland indicated that the proportion
of polyphyletic species was negatively correlated with the intensity of study,
indicating that inadequate taxonomy might have inflated their results. Other
studies of marine invertebrates have also found low rates of introgression
(e.g., \cite{Meyer2005-evolution}). Features of the life history of marine
invertebrates could lead to low effective population sizes (e.g., fluctuations
in population sizes, unequal contributions to the reproductive pool), in turn
causing the rapid sorting of mitochondrial lineages into reciprocally
monophyletic clades. However, a recent study \cite{Stoeckle2014}, showed that
the intra-specific levels of genetic variation in mitochondrial markers are much
lower than is expected from the neutral theory, suggesting that strong purifying
selection plays a significant role in shaping variation in mitochondrial
genes. Therefore, other factors, possibly specific to sea cucumbers, or marine
invertebrates, might influence the range of variation observed in COI.

Overall, even if 10\% of sea cucumber species do not form reciprocally
monophyletic clades, only 2.5\% are actually paraphyletic. Therefore, for
identification purposes, barcoding in sea cucumbers will be very accurate.

While the biological species concept recognizes reproductive isolation as the
key factor to delineate species, this criteria is not directly available to
taxonomists, and morphological and genetic information are used as proxies to
assess species limits. However, if reproductive isolation leads to genetic and
morphological differentiation, these three processes operate on different time
scales and are constrained by different evolutionary forces. These criteria may
not be in agreement and may not be indicative of species limits. Barcoding
allows to identify species groups that are characterized by these patterns, and
that deserve to be investigated further.

